n":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to speak loudly"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be public, to be conspicuous, to become apparent"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to publish, to disclose, to make public, to reveal what was concealed; to cause attention to be brought to, to be showy or make a spectacle of, to publicize or public show of","examples":[{"text":"قُلِ ادْعُوا اللَّهَ أَوِ ادْعُوا الرَّحْمَٰنَ ۖ أَيًّا مَّا تَدْعُوا فَلَهُ الْأَسْمَاءُ الْحُسْنَىٰ ۚ وَلَا تَجْهَرْ بِصَلَاتِكَ وَلَا تُخَافِتْ بِهَا وَابْتَغِ بَيْنَ ذَٰلِكَ سَبِيلًا","english":"Say: Call on God or call on the all-Encompassing; whatever that you may call, the characteristics which are best belong to Him. And do not make a spectacle of you keeping close to God nor make a mystery of it, but cause yourselves to behoove from a course between that."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to publish, to disclose, to make public, to reveal what was concealed; to dazzle, to confuse the sight of, to surprise by an early attack and sudden loud voice"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to discover ocularly, to see without a veil, to regard without any veil intervening"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to deem numerous, to see in great number"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to admire for its number or size, to value highly, to honor"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to clean a well, to hit on water, to remove the mud from"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to estimate approximately, to guess at"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to shake the milk bag to make butter"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to travel over, to traverse"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَهَرَ (jahara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of جَهَرَ (jahara)."},"ipa":["/d͡ʒa.ha.ra/","/d͡ʒahr/"]}